/*
~We talk about the planes like they are places to visit, but they are literally the afterlife! They are where our stories, myths, and dreams play themselves out! Contemplate having the stuff of myth, transmuted to actual blood, running in your veins.~
~And the forbear of the Argent name was not some middling devil or deva, but a solar! Practically a god! Trust me, you cannot imagine what is like to have such lineage!~
~Well...~
~You seriously don't know who you are talking to.~
~People discuss it like a blessing, but mortals are not meant to be made of such stuff. It is so hard... it takes an iron will to master your own blood, every day. Some can do so... not me, but some. Some even find power in it, use it to propel themselves to greatness. Or at least, that is what they tell themselves. But is it truly great, to use a gift of someone else's making? Can you claim superiority, for something fused in your blood?~
~You asked about Caelar... I worry for her. She was always so strong, she mastered her gift so completely, so young. But now - she acts as if she has earned it. She talks about mastering fate itself. Like a god! But she is still a mortal; and I wonder, is she really so powerful, or is she foolishly listening to the whispers in her blood, the echoes of power from another time, another place?~
~We...~
