@30024 = ~What? I would not do that!~
@30025 = ~That is stupid. I could not have done if even if I wanted to.~
@30026 = ~I know that, but the witnesses are apparently quite clear. In the last day you have defeated Caelar's lieutenants, you traveled to another plane of existence, reportedly fought an archfiend... such things are not done by ordinary people. Given who... given what you are...~
@30027 = ~Just because my father was Bhaal, that doesn't mean I can teleport from here to a distant city and back. That's ridiculous. It doesn't work that way.~
@30028 = ~Honestly? If pressed, I'm not sure I could say what you are and aren't capable of.~
@30029 = ~Anyway why would I? I've been busy here, as you well know. It makes no sense. Skie is, well, not a friend exactly, but... I don't know. Certainly not someone I want dead! Have they raised her yet? Just ask her, she will tell you.~
@30030 = ~I am told she cannot be raised. It is not clear why. Nothing they tried has worked. They told me it is as if her soul is not available for the spells to work on. This started as a war, but now we have been dealing with godchildren and devils and - I don't know what to think.~
@30031 = ~I am not here to act against you. We have been through too much, and I told them I would not do so. But you have been officially ordered back to Baldur's Gate, to speak to the Dukes. I am to ensure you comply. You are not under arrest. It is more of a firm invitation. It will give you a chance to clear things up.~
@30032 = ~Very well. Let us go back to Baldur's Gate.~
@30033 = ~I don't envy you - I would not want to face Entar Silvershield right now. He is a powerful warrior, with a powerful temper. And he has a long and antagonistic history with those who followed your, uh, sire. At any rate, no sense delaying the inevitable. Let us go.~
