@30041 = ~<CHARNAME>. Thank you for coming here on such short notice. We have received reports of your successes in the field on the way to Castle Dragonspear. And of what transpired therein. Your accomplishments on behalf of Baldur's Gate are noted, and appreciated.~ // belt dialogue in palace
@30042 = ~However, such doings do not put anyone above the law. And to be frank with you, those accomplishments are the only reason we are having this conversation freely, like civilized people. We have witnesses claiming to have seen you commit a most foul murder. Their stories have been magically scrutinized, and found to be honest. We need an explanation.~ // belt
@30043 = ~We need more than that! We need justice! This goes well beyond murder! Murder is reversible - Bhaal's reprehensible followers made a game of it. But this - this! What was done here is unnatural!~ // entar
@30044 = ~<CHARNAME>, Powerful magic was employed in the murder. It has so far escaped our capacity to undo it. I don't know how much you have been told. It is less that Skie's body was killed, as her soul was ripped from her body. Her body now lies preserved, but impossible to revive. If you can give us assistance, or information, about what was done to Skie, it would go a long way toward establishing your credibility.~ // liia
@30045 = ~I wasn't here, I was at Dragonspear Castle. How could I know what happened?~ // ignorant answer
@30046 = ~Before Sarevok was killed, I found an enchanted mirror... it had the power to make reflections of people. Could something like that work to trap Skie's spirit?~ // answer about mirror shard, if Global("D5PartyHadShard","GLOBAL",1)
@30047 = ~In Durlag's Tower I found a fiend with a dagger that had somehow trapped the essence of a powerful demon. The demon was freed, but I defeated it.~ // answer about soultaker dagger, if Global("D5PartyHadSoultaker","GLOBAL",2)
@30048 = ~~ // 
@30049 = ~~
@30050 = ~Hmm... what you describe sounds like a Mirror of Opposition. A powerful artifact, to be certain, but almost the opposite of what happened here. This might be related to the effects of another powerful mirror artifact, a Mirror of Life Trapping... but you have not described encountering anything like that.~ // liia
@30051 = ~Interesting. I have heard of artifacts that could seize and contain mortal souls, and use them to fuel magical power or effects. It is not unheard of. And you say this had something to do with summoning a fiend? Do you know where the dagger is now?~ // liia
@30052 = ~No. It was stolen by the demon's cultists and used to free it. In the chaos of the battle and my desperation to make sure the demon could not escape to wreak havoc on the realms, I lost track of what happened to the dagger.~
@30053 = ~Freeing such a powerful trapped entity will usually break the magic of the artifact. Or, even if this dagger were still usable, if it was connected to Skie's murder we should be able to divine its location without much difficulty. It would take truly mighty magic to prevent it - mightier magic than you are capable of.~ // liia
@30054 = ~We have no idea what this individual is capable of! The blood of a god of murder runs in <PRO_HISHER> veins! You all heard the reports of the event at Boareskyr Bridge! Nothing can be taken for granted - <CHARNAME> must be detained and subjected to forced interrogation!~ // entar
@30055 = ~It is not just the matter of Skie - I have looked into <CHARNAME> here. The first accounts of <PRO_HISHER> deeds on the Coast Way coincide with My son Eddard's death! <CHARNAME> is persecuting my family! My achievements against Bhaalist sects in my early career are well known - this must be some long-simmering revenge plot!~ // entar
@30056 = ~<CHARNAME>, you must understand the delicacy of our position, here. If you cannot provide any information that helps the investigation... well, we can take no chances.~ // belt
@30057 = ~I wish I could tell you more. Please, let me assist in the investigation. This is my good name we are talking about, and I had no grudge against Skie. Let me help get to the bottom of this.~
@30058 = ~I do not like what you imply, Duke Belt. They tried to trap me at Dragonspear, and in Avernus, and all failed. I will not be imprisoned!~
@30059 = ~A revenge decades in the making, enacted against children wholly ignorant of its origin? That...makes no sense.~
@30060 = ~~
@37012  = ~I have looked into it - Eddard was killed on the Coast Way right around the time this person left Candlekeep! And now my daughter is gone!~
@38008  = ~Alright, sir. I rushed here to find Lord Entar, to tell you that someone has confessed to the attack on your daughter! They are in custody right now! Only...~
@38010  = ~Well, that's the thing, sir. It... well, it is <CHARNAME>. Walked right into Headquarters, said something about <PRO_HISHER> purpose being fulfilled, and that <PRO_HESHE> had no reason to run. I put <PRO_HIMHER> into a cell, and came straight here to inform you. Only, now I see <CHARNAME> before me... but how? That cell is warded against magical escape!~
@38011  = ~<CHARNAME> has been here with us for some time now. And was brought here directly from Dragonspear Castle after dispatching the Crusade. I assure you <PRO_HESHE> has had no opportunity to make a stop at the Flaming Fist.~ // belt
@38012  = ~We do not know what <PRO_HESHE> is capable of! I demand that <PRO_HESHE> be incarcerated until we know what <PRO_HESHE> is up to! I will have justice for Skie!~ // entar
@38058  = ~Yeah, well I was a smart kid! Oh <CHARNAME>, it really is you! Thank Tymora! But, huh. How did you get in there in the first place?? Ooooh... did you kill Skie?? Wait, then who was helping the Coalition at Dragonspear Castle?~
@38059  = ~I did! I mean, the Dragonspear part. I didn't kill Skie! Imoen, I don't know what happened. I switched places, somehow, earlier today. I was over there, and I blinked, and I was here. I didn't feel myself teleporting or anything like that. It felt like... I didn't change, the whole world changed around me. What could do that?~
